		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;06/13/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 01:00:22</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=6072"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=6072')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=39504&amp;TOPIC_ID=4958&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Pre%2Dnerf+CoS+%2D+Top+3+reasons+why+I+value+mine%2E&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         CoS or PRCoS = Circlet of Shadows, or Pre-Nerf Circlet of Shadows.<BR>The quick story: <BR>This circlet that's a headpeice goes on your head and has minor stats, but has the awesome ability of casting normal invis /instantly/. Just like the effect of Jboots. Punch the button 100 times in a row if you want and the entire time you see all the little bubbles and such, you're still invis.<BR>Sometime later, this circlet got nerfed. The cast time became like, 2 seconds or something (dunno, never saw a new one). So the useability of it dropped by about 90 percent. The coolest part of the original circlet was that since it was an instant cast time, you could FD with aggro.. then hop up and invis with the circlet so fast that the mobs wouldn't regain aggro (most of the time anyway, some mobs are a pain).<BR>So anyway, that's why people value their pre-nerf Circlet of Shadows so much. The price on each server seems to vary hugely. On Innoruuk, I remember seeing them go for about 2k whereas I've heard stories of other servers having them go for 15-20k. Shadow Knights can use them as well, which makes them even better pullers IMO. But for some reason, Necros seem to be the biggest users.<BR>Btw, you can use it from an inventory slot which (again, like jboots) is the second best thing about it. Freeing up 1) your head slot for some real +int +mana/+hp items and 2) a spell slot so that you never have to mem invis again. :)</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=205091" target="_blank"><font color=red><font size=5>Ashtaroth Solarium</font id=size5></font id=red></a><BR><i>Nec-Romancer of Innoruuk</i><BR><i>Legends of the Realm</i><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

